**Intuitive design**

From top to bottom the app is designed very simple. It allows you to navigate, users should be able to navigate, clear, and type in information by using the organised buttons. Accessibility ensures that the app is useable making the app more understandable.

**Content prioritisation**

Necessary elements are included to make the app function good. This makes it easier for the user to use the app without any complications. When elements are in place and order it makes the app run smooth with no difficulties.

**Legible Text Content**

Content is fairly legible making it easy for users to read what is being displayed. With a readable font size users will not struggle to see what they’re reading.

**Make Interface Elements Clearly Visible**

The user will be able to see all components on the screen, components are not crowded, there is space between each component, this shows the neatness of the app with no components all over the place

**Hand Position Controls**

Each button is in a position where it can be easily accessed by users, users should just know what button to use. Users can see and touch the buttons on the screen with no complications
